JOHANNESBURG - A tough day is in store for some Joburg residents as City Power has announced a 10-hour power cut in Lenasia on Wednesday. This is due to national grid maintenance work taking place around the area. CityPower spokesperson Isaac Mangena said the interruptions were expected to start from 7 am until 5 pm: “And it will affect several areas and certain main streets in the area.” Download the Eyewitness News app to your iOS  or Android device.